New World Resources, Czech Coal Producer, Drops After Earnings

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-02-24T08:16:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/new-world-resources-czech-coal-producer-drops-after-earnings.html
  New World Resources NV , the biggest
Czech supplier of coal to steelmakers, fell in  London , snapping
two days of gains, after posting fourth-quarter earnings.  The stock tumbled as much a 6.4 percent and traded down 1.7
percent at 908 pence as of 8:11 a.m. in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  